args:
Deep within an ancient ruin, the party finds
a gateway linking back to Alfonse's world.
However, Loki and Harle soon arrive intent
on its destruction. The princes' parties then
join forces to battle the imperial army and
save the world.
This is an imperial research facility.\nThey were apparently studying some\nsort of alchemy here.
Could that be the method they used\nto create the Uncanny Gate?
Unknown. The method used to summon\nthe wicked demon a thousand years ago\nhas been lost to time.
Although we DO know Dyrenell alchemists\nattempted to revive the technique some\nthree hundred years ago.
However, there exists no mention of the\ndegree of their success, if any.
What IS certain is that research was\nconducted into the Uncanny Gate at this\nfacility, so we should search for clues.
Uuuugh! Reading is for the birds.
And yet, we've no choice but to search\nthrough every musty tome in case the\ninformation we seek is inside.
Disagreeable? Wait, this can't be...\nPrince {player_name}, please\nhave a look at this!
Let me see... Wait, what in the world?!\nThis book mentions the Askran Kingdom!
As I thought. I still lack proficiency in\nreading your language, so I worried I\nmay have been mistaken.
The data here is three hundred years old.\nApparently they were trying to create an\nUncanny Gate, but couldn't get it to work.
However, it DOES seem they were able to\nbriefly connect to another world and speak\nwith someone on the other side.
According to this book, that person\nclaimed to be from Askr.
So if we can make that spooky gate\nwhatever appear, these guys can use\nit to go home! ...Er, right?
But they never actually completed it.\nIs it really gonna work?
If this gate is like those in our world,\nPrince Alfonse may be able to open it.
Then where do we find this gate?
According to this, it is housed in a facility\nthat has since fallen into ruin.
Right then. Everybody get your best\nruin-diving gear on!
If the documents are correct, there ought\nto be some vestiges of it here, yes.
To think we would be called to make\nuse of such unsavory technology...
Look, let's just find the thing, use it,\nand get outta here already, okay?\nThis place gives me the willies.
I don't see anything gate-like\naround here.
Hey, awesome. It's a pile of rocks.
These are not merely stones;\nthey are the remains of a gate.
Aw, maaan! We came all this way\nand the thing is BUSTED?!
Not quiteâ€”I can feel a faint power\nemanating from it. Perhaps I can...
Yes...I think it will work. It does have the\nsame feel as the gates in my world.
It may take some time to open it,\nbut I think this will take us home!
This is a huge relief for all of us.
How curious to think our worlds have\nactually been connected for so long.
I suppose that IS a little strange...\nbut since it let us become friends,\nI'm certainly glad about it.
Uh, guys? We got about a kajillion\nimperial soldiers headed this way,\nand they ain't lookin' to play nice.
By Ilia, look at their numbers...
Did they know we were here?
Goodness me, aren't you just a bunch of\nsharp-sighted lads and lasses to have\ndiscovered this old, mouldering ruin!
I know you have come here to stop us\nfrom returning to our world, Loki!
SUCH a clever boyâ€”I really should enter\nyou in a village talent show sometime.\nBut it's true: If you leave, my fun ends.
Of course! Madness? Chaos? Evil gates?\nIt's fun on a bun that's left out in the sun!
So yer just playin' us for cheap laughs?\nThat's the worst!
Loki's goal may have been naught but\nmischief, but I wager the Empire has\na more tangible aim in mind.

Our great Empress has incredible depths
of knowledge and foresight; your poor
brains are likely to overheat if you spend
too much time trying to reason it out.
Chaos is not without its own purposesâ€”\nand the Empire will use that chaos to\nexpand to ever greater heights!
Tee hee hee! Oh, but this has been\neven more fun than I dared hope!
Are you saying the current rash of\nbizarre events was something YOU\norchestrated?
Even supposing I didâ€”which I'm not\nsaying by the wayâ€”it was YOUR powers\nthat actually caused all of this misery.
Perhaps so. But in that case, we will pay\nthat debt to this world by defeating you\nhere and now!
To leave you would mean countless\nproblems for the people of this world.
Agreed. Let us defeat Loki here\nand pay our debt for good and all!
Oh, what a righteous and principled\nbunch you are!

Yet words are but wind, my princes and
princesses; actions are another thing
entirely. Do you truly think you can
back up these bold words of yours?
I'll kill you with my own hands, Loki.\nBut you'll suffer first. A lot.
Good heavens, you are a confused bunch.\nLet me clear this up for you: You will be\nattacking nothing. You are BEING attacked.
We will assault those ruins, destroy this\ngate, and ensure that you've no choice\nbut to remain in this world forever!
You will be a pestilence that sweeps over\nthis land, leaving naught but terror and\nchaos in your wake!
Hmm... Speaking of which, I wonder just\nhow much of our assault these paltry little\nruins can withstand before crumbling.
We will defeat youâ€”the power of the\nfriendships we forged will see to it!
We will protect the bond\nbetween our worlds!
